node.text:
I was craving something sweet for dessert so I whipped together this creamy Strawberry Tahini Smoothie Bowl #sponsoredbyninja. I topped it with berries, kiwi, hemp hearts and cacao nibs. This is something I wouldn’t mind having for breakfast when I’m in the mood for something sweet! I easily made it in my Ninja® Foodi®Smoothie Bowl Maker.
.
This awesome device has a built-in tamper to blend and power through frozen and solid foods with less liquid for the thickest of smoothie bowls. 
.
The smartTORQUE™ is designed to power through heavy loads without stalling or the need to stir or shake. It makes the most thickest, and creamiest smoothies.
.
Strawberry Tahini Smoothie Bowl!
.
1 Frozen Banana 🍌.
1/2 cup Frozen Strawberries 🍓.
1 tablespoon honey 🍯 or maple syrup. 
1/2 cup oats.
1/4 cup tahini.
1/4 cup - 1/2 cup oat milk.
.
Add all ingredients to the @ninjakitchen Ninja® Foodi®Smoothie Bowl Maker. Turn on and press the bowl button. Blend all ingredients well and turn the built-in tamper a few times to make sure it’s fully blended. Add to a bowl and top with all your favorite toppings. Find out more about the Ninja® Foodi®Smoothie Bowl Maker by clicking the link in my bio! #NinjaFoodiBlender

node.text:
#ad My family and I have been loving these @newmansown Cauliflower Crust Thin and Crispy Pizzas. My favorite is the Margherita, but also comes in a Cheese variety. It’s made with real cauliflower, real mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses, ripe tomatoes, and olive oil. I bake it in the oven, straight on the rack, for 12 minutes on 425 F and it comes out perfectly crispy every time! It’s also certified gluten-free.
.
Go visit @newmansown for the store locator to find out where to get your hands on some crispy crust cauliflower pizza goodness. #NewmansOwnPartner

node.title: Newman’s Own Cauliflower Crust Thin & Crispy Pizza

node.text: I’m extremely happy about how delicious this Vegetable Coconut Korma turned out! I used @mayakaimalfoods Coconut Korma Indian Simmer Sauce and Turmeric Cumin Surekha Rice and it was super easy to make in less then 20 minutes.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Marlena Kur on August 23, 2021 tagging @thetahinigoddess. May be an image of food.

node.text:
The veggie cravings were coming on strong so a big bowl of veggies for lunch today was a must. In this bowl I have toaster oven roasted sweet potatoes, chili roasted chickpeas and sautéed garlic broccoli florets drizzled with tzatziki tahini and topped with crumbled feta and fresh parsley.  It was so darn good! 
.
🍠 For the toaster oven roasted sweet potato, peel and cut sweet potato into 1-2 inch pieces. Spread onto baking sheet, toss with olive oil and bake or air fry on 425 F for 15-18 minutes. 
.
🥦 For the broccoli heat a little olive oil and/or butter in a pan. Add the broccoli and sauté for 3-4 minutes until broccoli starts to char. Season with salt and garlic powder (or fresh garlic) and continue to sauté until the broccoli is tender. If needed add a splash of water to the hot pan to soften the broccoli if you prefer it that way.
.
For the chickpeas follow the same steps as the sweet potatoes but cook for 12 minutes until crispy. You can season the chickpeas as desired but you can also find the recipe for the chili roasted chickpeas with the link in my bio.
.
Add all the cooked veggies to a bowl, drizzle with tahini and top with crumbled feta. I used @thetahinigoddess Tzatziki tahini. Hope you’re having a great day!

node.text:
Brunch plate with flaked garlic and herb salmon 🐟 over mixed greens 🥬 with lemony white beans, cherry tomatoes 🍅, olives 🫒, hard boiled egg 🥚 and mashed avocado drizzled with extra virgin olive oil and a squeeze of fresh lemon juice. 
.
I made the salmon in a foil packet with lemon slices, fresh garlic, fresh chopped dill, fresh chopped parsley, olive oil and cracked black pepper which can be cooked in a 400 F oven or on the grill for 12-15 minutes for a naturally buttery and flaky goodness! It’s so delicious and an easy way to make salmon. Hope your having a wonderful day!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marlena Kur on August 20, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: I had some leftover rotisserie chicken, pre-made hard boiled eggs and half of an unused avocado in the fridge so it was a perfect opportunity to make this Cobb salad with lemon Dijon dressing! To make the dressing add 2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil, 1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice, 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder to a small mason jar, close the lid and shake well until creamy. It was a delicious and nourishing lunch! Hope you’re having a great day.

node.text:
This Grilled Chili Lime Shrimp Salad really hit the spot. Fresh and flavorful perfect for a hot summer day! Here’s how I made it:
.
Add some peeled and deveined shrimp to a bowl. Toss with olive oil, chili lime seasoning, garlic powder and fresh lime juice. Prepare a grill or heat a grill pan. Place shrimp on grill and cook on each side for 3-4 minutes until pink and lightly charred. In a skillet on the stovetop heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Add 1 cup cooked corn kernels and season with chili lime seasoning. Cook the corn in the pan stirring occasionally until it becomes golden and toasty. In a large bowl add some chopped romaine lettuce. Top with charred corn, grilled shrimp, cherry tomatoes, avocado and minced red onion. Drizzle in some extra virgin olive oil and squeeze in some fresh lime juice. Season with sea salt and garnish with fresh chopped cilantro. It’s so darn tasty. Hope you’re having an amazing day!

node.text:
Slow Sunday’s call for Cinnamon Sweet Potato Waffles 🧇 with fresh berries 🍓🫐, crispy bacon 🥓, avocado 🥑 and a fried egg! 
.
These Cinnamon Sweet Potato Waffles 🧇 are soft and fluffy with just the right amount of sweetness and slight crispiness on the edges. Here’s how to make them:
.
Ingredients:
1 Large sweet potato.
1 cup of all purpose flour (sub gluten free)
1 tablespoon sweetener of choice.
1 teaspoon baking powder.
1 teaspoon cinnamon.
1 egg.
1 cup milk of choice.
1 tablespoon coconut oil.
1 teaspoon pure vanilla.
.
(1) Poke holes in the sweet potato (with peel left on) with a fork in 2-3 spots around the potato. Loosely wrap the sweet potato in a paper towel, place on a microwave safe plate and microwave on high for 4 1/2 minutes. Carefully slice the hot potato in half, let cool. 
(2) Heat your waffle iron to medium high heat. Use a spoon to scoop the cooked sweet potato out of the peel, add to a bowl and mash well. Add the flour, sweetener, baking powder and cinnamon and combine. 
(3) Add the remaining wet ingredients and mix well until it forms a batter like consistency. A few lumps in the batter is ok. (4) Pour ladle fulls of the batter into your waffle iron and cook each waffle 5-6 minutes depending on your waffle iron until the waffles are golden and fluffy. Makes 3-4 servings. Hope you’re having an amazing day!

node.text:
This Beet Panzanella salad 🥗 made with @lovebeets organic cooked beets is a wonderful way to enjoy the last few weeks of summer. Love Beets are on sale at Publix through 8/17 so now is a great opportunity to make this scrumptious salad. 
.
Those cherishing evenings eating outside with family and friends in the backyard around a fire pit with a cool breeze are the most funnest of times! This salad is fresh and cozy but most importantly it taste gooood!
.
To make the Summer Beet Panzanella Salad combine the following ingredients into a bowl. 
.
- 1/2 cup @lovebeets cut into 1 inch pieces. 
- 1 cup cherry tomatoes 🍅 sliced in half. 
- 1 cup English cucumber 🥒 cut into 1 inch pieces.
- 1/2 cup yellow bell pepper (or any color bell pepper) cut into 1 inch pieces. 
- 1/2 cup pitted kalamata olives or green castelventrano olives 🫒 . 
- 1/4 cup thin sliced red onion 🧅 .
- Feta cheese, goat cheese or fresh mozzarella balls your choice 🧀. 
- Loaf bread like a baguette 🥖, Italian or French bread cut into 1-2 inch cubes. 
- Extra virgin olive oil for drizzling.
- 1-2 tablespoons lemon 🍋 juice. 
- 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar. 
- Fresh basil 🌿 for garnish.
- salt and pepper.
. 
(1) Arrange bread cubes onto a sheet pan. Drizzle on olive oil, season with salt and pepper. Toss to combine and bake on 400 for 10 minutes until lightly toasty ….or toast in toaster oven for 4-5 minutes or until lightly golden. 
(2) In a large bowl combine @lovebeets organic cooked beets, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, bell pepper and kalamata olives. Drizzle in some olive oil, a few splashes of red wine vinegar and a few generous squeezes of fresh lemon juice. Toss together to combine. 
(3) Add the toasted bread to the bowl and lightly toss in the salad mixture to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Top with cheese and fresh basil. Serves 2-4.
